British Telecommunications Plc &lt;BTY.L>will market electronic data transmission equipment of its owndesign in North America, a spokesman said.    The spokesman told Reuters the equipment, known asfourth-generation modems, will be sold by &lt;Mitel Datacom Inc>,a wholly-owned subsidiary of Canada's Mitel Corp &lt;MLT.TO>, inwhich British Telecom has a controlling stake.    He declined to comment on the volume of projected sales. Hesaid the modems, already available in Europe where they hold amajority share of the market, were the first of their kind tocomply with the latest international standards. Reuter&#3;